# Rope Crane Pier — Illustration Prompt

Create a richly detailed, roughly square digital painting sized to sit beside narrative text on desktop or mobile screens. Depict a grounded late-medieval harbor campaign setting with hawsers, cranes, bollards, piers, iron hooks, wet planks, and labor gangs. Emphasize crisp readability, brighter maritime color accents, and clear spatial separation more than muddy painterly atmosphere.

- Composition: long working pier with multiple branch routes and strong depth toward the tower and berth.
- Key elements: suspended rope crane, huge coiled warps, capstan direction branching off, and slip-side fittings nearby.
- Character focus: quay workers speaking as if all motion is inevitable while the smallest omitted detail still matters.
- Navigation hint: make visible routes toward Signal Beacon Tower, Capstan Walk, and Boatyard Slip readable in the image.

